node.text:
Hi there friends, 
So today is day 173 off of Valium that the doctors had me on for over a decade. I have been in a wave the last couple of days from this benzo brain injury which has included nausea and vomiting, disassociation, derealization, dizziness, a spinny feeling like I just got off of the gravatron at the fair and the feeling of being on a big rocking boat in the ocean which has been incessant for the last 48 hours. 😞 The doctors took me off of the Maximum dose of Valium in less than 4 days and I think that is why I am having such a hard time. However, I have had days and even weeks wave free. For now I am just going to rest and ride this damn thing because that’s my only choice. Please remember that everyone else’s symptoms in benzo withdrawal do NOT mean that they will happen to you. I am just here to share my personal journey and try and help others going through this. Sending love to anyone else out there experiencing a wave. 🌊 This too shall pass. .
